			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I hit level 52 recently and I have been exploring the many different uses of the fire pet. One thing I found is it works pretty well with kiting groups... The usual kiting group I am in has a kiter (druid or bard, etc) running the mob around a group of nukers with pets in tow with /pet taunt off. The fire pet will root the mob so this means you better be the only pet user in group or have the other pet owners /pet back off (most kiting groups kite mobs that would tear a pet up in a couple of rounds). Still the fire pet works really well in this environment. 
<br />

<br />
I found a way to solo with the fire pet that is more efficient than the 51 earth pet. Give your pet one of those weighty polearms and a full set of summoned focus gear and summoned armor in the slots he has left (belt of ... and muzzle of mardu work great if you can find in the bazaar). Then get your pet a virtue or temp...  The pet can melee pretty well and nukes hard on top of all that. You can handle things with this pet a little easier than with your 51 earth but the REAL key (I tested this off a rumor I have heard) is to get a class that can mana drain (enchanter preferably) and /duel them and /pet back off over and over while the enchanter mana drains the pet.... as soon as his damage shield wears off (it's very short term) he -WILL- cast the 49 fire pet damage shield!!!! This makes your pet a melee beast with all the equipment you gave him. 
<br />

<br />
Tell me what you think of my findings so far.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
