			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well, I did a little testing on seafurbies...
<br />

<br />
Pets were supplied with an OoW pet kit (though PoP toys would have proc-ed), BO3, and did not need heals during battle and effectively "soloed" the mobs. All mobs were pulled with Malosinia. Parsing the 52 Fire was problematic as its melee is very inconsistent. Taunt was on for all pets. Shown is:
<br />
Kill time, combat-time DPS (melee only, no spells, no DS, no procs, as per EQ Companion). 
<br />

<br />
Not once did I see the pet buff with anything other than Greater Shielding, Steelskin, and the two O'Keils spells (though I could not mana drain the pet).
<br />

<br />
49 Fire (Torch):
<br />
1:26, 40
<br />
1:32, 35
<br />
1:36, 37
<br />
1:32, 37
<br />
1:26, 43
<br />

<br />
51 Earth (unfocused):
<br />
1:48, 38
<br />
1:33, 46
<br />
1:46, 40
<br />
1:39, 44
<br />
1:45, 40
<br />

<br />
52 Fire (unfocused):
<br />
2:23, 25
<br />
2:29, 22
<br />
2:19, 24
<br />
2:14, 24
<br />
2:07, 28
<br />
2:15, 22
<br />

<br />
This suggests that the 52 Fire pet is less effective than the 49 Fire pet, in situations where DS damage comes into play. 52 Fire is also less effective than 51 Earth in this situation.
<br />

<br />
This seems to fit with my recollection of the lower 50s -- stick with 49 pets until you get 53 Air. 
<br />

<br />
(Earlier parsing with unfocused 49 Air and BO3 only, so no mask or stat boosts from pet kit, had it doing a very comparable 39 DPS against seafurbies and would probably have kill times not much slower than 51 Earth, with no root being cast in a kiting situation.)
<br />

<br />

<br />
Now, maybe I'm missing something with this mana-drain approach, but...<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.sovereignguild.org/forum/viewtopic.php?t=4429" target="_blank" class="postlink">Master Elementalist Itchyban of Veeshan</a>
<br />
"Nothing to see here. Move along. Move along." 
<br />
"These are not the droids you are looking for."</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
