			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">The main problem with attempting to use any of the 52+ fire pets to do anything 'interesting' or unique, is that the pets behavior as far as what spells it casts and when, is so unpredictable as to be unreliable.
<br />

<br />
When you want it to snare, it'll root. When you want it to root, it'll nuke. When you want it to do dps, it'll chain dispell. You never know what it's going to do (other than suck).
<br />

<br />
Root is the absolute worst thing to do in any kiting group, especially if you have melee or pets beating on the mob while it's chasing the kiter. Mob instantly stops and starts beating on the melee/pet. Completely eliminating the reason for kiting in the first place (avoid taking melee dmg from the mobs).
<br />

<br />
A bit of randomness adds a spice to the game that makes it enjoyable, but having random unpredictable behavior from your own pet negates any potential benefits.
<br />

<br />
Enjoy your 10pp pet (at 5s 2c per pet, you'll go thru that much in malachite attempting to solo the same mobs with the 52pet as you would with the 49 or 51 pets).<br />_________________<br />Master Elementalist Sebboh Nivlac
<br />
Officer of Only the Brave, Veeshan
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=408189" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=408189</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
